            <div type="translation">
            <p>Arnth Remzna, son of Arnth, zilath of the scupitnues.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>Remzna appears as a common name in Hellenistic Chiusi. The Colle necropolis attests
                    other members of this family, likely a wealthy one capable of affording such an
                    elaborate cinerary urn. Zilath elsewhere denotes a high magistrate, while
                    Remznaâ€™s attire identifies him as belonging to a priestly order. The term
                    scuptinues, which is unique, may therefore refer to a specific priestly group.
                    For the description of the body of the urn, cf. Turfa (2005).</p></div>
            

